.TH "xxxfb_cursor" 9 "xxxfb_cursor" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xxxfb_cursor \- OPTIONAL. If your hardware lacks support for a cursor, leave this field NULL.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xxxfb_cursor
.BI "(struct fb_info *info "  ","
.BI "struct fb_cursor *cursor "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "info" 12
frame buffer structure that represents a single frame buffer
.IP "cursor" 12
structure defining the cursor to draw.

This operation is used to set or alter the properities of the
cursor.

Returns negative errno on error, or zero on success.
